+# Change Summary: entry-canvas
+
+> Auto-generated summary after all waves complete.
+
+---
+
+## Intent
+
+Add the project entry point — `index.html`, `src/main.ts`, `src/types.ts` — so `npm run dev` boots a browser and `npm run build` produces a deployable `dist/`. Resolves c2's `UNRESOLVED_ENTRY` error.
+
+## Output Files
+
+| File | Action |
+|------|--------|
+| `index.html` | Create |
+| `src/main.ts` | Create |
+| `src/types.ts` | Create |
+
+## Key Decisions
+
+- **`index.html` is plain static HTML**: dark background, fixed-position HUD overlay (top-left), 480×480 canvas placeholder, `<script type="module" src="/src/main.ts">`. Inline `<style>` for now; refactor to `.css` in ph.6 when responsive layout is needed.
+- **`src/main.ts` is minimal**: get canvas, fill with floor gray (`#888888` per NFR-3), log "Sokoban ready". No game loop, no state, no input — all deferred to ph.3+.
+- **`src/types.ts` provides shared types** (`Direction`, `Coord`, `Tile`, `Intent` discriminated union) for ph.2+ to consume. `Coord` is `readonly` to prevent accidental mutation in the reducer. `Intent` is additive — ph.2 may extend it without breaking existing callers.
+- **Canvas size 480×480 placeholder**: ph.3 will compute tile size from level dimensions dynamically; ph.6 will add DPR handling.
+
+## Verification Results
+
+- Type check: **`npx tsc --noEmit` exits 0**
+- Tests: **`npx vitest run` exits 0** (1/1 smoke test still passing)
+- Build: **`npm run build` exits 0**; produced `dist/index.html` (0.75 kB) and `dist/assets/index-6G2uMDa0.js` (0.94 kB)
+
+## Verification Commands Run
+
+```bash
+npx tsc --noEmit        # exit 0
+npm run build           # exit 0; dist/index.html + dist/assets/*.js
+npx vitest run          # exit 0; 1 test in 1 file
+```
+
+## Browser verification
+
+Not testable in this environment (no headless browser). `npm run dev` boots the Vite dev server on port 5173 — opening it in a browser shows a 480×480 gray canvas and "Sokoban ready" in console. Manual verification recommended before ph.2.
+
+## Readiness for ph.2
+
+ph.2 (core-engine) is now unblocked: `src/types.ts` provides the foundational types, `index.html` provides the runtime context, and the build pipeline produces a deployable bundle. ph.2 will add `src/core/reducer.ts`, `src/core/move.ts`, `src/core/winCheck.ts`, `src/core/history.ts` with full TDD coverage.
