+# Design: entry-canvas
+
+> Technical design for adding the project entry point.
+
+---
+
+## Context & Goals
+
+This change adds the minimum files needed for Vite to find an entry point: `index.html` (the HTML shell), `src/main.ts` (the JS entry), and `src/types.ts` (shared types for later phases).
+
+**Constraints** (from `ph.1-foundation/context.md` D6):
+- Single `<canvas id="game">` for the game world
+- `<div id="hud">` placeholder for later HUD content
+- Static HTML; no bundler-rendered template
+- Canvas in CSS pixels (DPR handling deferred to ph.6)
+
+**Core goals** (3):
+1. `npm run build` produces `dist/index.html` + JS bundle (resolves c2's `UNRESOLVED_ENTRY` error)
+2. `npm run dev` boots Vite dev server without error
+3. `src/types.ts` provides foundational types (`Direction`, `Coord`, `Tile`) for ph.2 to consume
+
+---
+
+## Technical Approach
+
+Three files. No external libraries.
+
+### `index.html`
+
+```html
+<!doctype html>
+<html lang="en">
+  <head>
+    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
+    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
+    <title>Sokoban</title>
+    <style>
+      html, body { margin: 0; padding: 0; height: 100%; background: #1a1a1a; }
+      body { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: sans-serif; }
+      #game { display: block; background: #888; image-rendering: pixelated; }
+      #hud { position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; padding: 8px 12px; color: #eee; font-size: 14px; }
+    </style>
+  </head>
+  <body>
+    <div id="hud"></div>
+    <canvas id="game" width="480" height="480"></canvas>
+    <script type="module" src="/src/main.ts"></script>
+  </body>
+</html>
+```
+
+- Dark background (`#1a1a1a`) matches the "flat vector" aesthetic (walls are dark gray)
+- Canvas default size 480×480 (8 tiles × 60px, or 10 × 48 — ph.3 will set this dynamically based on level)
+- `image-rendering: pixelated` keeps tiles crisp at non-integer scales
+- HUD fixed-position overlay (top-left) — later phases fill it with move count, level name, win banner
+
+### `src/main.ts`
+
+```ts
+const canvas = document.getElementById('game') as HTMLCanvasElement | null;
+if (!canvas) throw new Error('Canvas element #game not found');
+
+const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
+if (!ctx) throw new Error('2D context not available');
+
+// Placeholder: fill canvas with floor color to confirm rendering works
+ctx.fillStyle = '#888888'; // floor gray per NFR-3
+ctx.fillRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
+
+console.log('Sokoban ready');
+```
+
+- DOM lookup with null-check (defensive — strict TS will complain otherwise)
+- Single `fillRect` proves Canvas 2D works
+- Console log gives a visible "ready" signal for dev verification
+- No game loop, no rAF, no state — all deferred to ph.3+
+
+### `src/types.ts`
+
+```ts
+export type Direction = 'N' | 'S' | 'E' | 'W';
+
+export interface Coord {
+  readonly x: number;
+  readonly y: number;
+}
+
+export type Tile = 'floor' | 'wall' | 'target';
+
+export type Intent =
+  | { type: 'move'; dir: Direction }
+  | { type: 'undo' }
+  | { type: 'reset' };
+```
+
+- `Direction` — string union; used as move direction in ph.2 reducer and as swipe-detection output in ph.6
+- `Coord` — readonly grid coordinate; `readonly` prevents accidental mutation in reducer (a common bug source)
+- `Tile` — discriminated union for level data; will expand in ph.3 to include box, player, etc.
+- `Intent` — discriminated union for the input pipeline (per architecture research Section: Input pipeline)
+
+Pure types only; no runtime code.
+
+---
+
+## File Manifest
+
+| File Path | Description | Action |
+|-----------|-------------|--------|
+| `index.html` | HTML entry; canvas + HUD + module script | Create |
+| `src/main.ts` | JS entry; get canvas, draw placeholder, log ready | Create |
+| `src/types.ts` | Shared types: Direction, Coord, Tile, Intent | Create |
+
+---
+
+## Test Strategy
+
+No tests in this change. The next change `c4` is smoke-test related (mostly redundant after c1). Real tests for game logic come in ph.2 (core engine) with type:behavior tasks.
+
+### Verification
+
+- [ ] `npm run build` exits 0 and produces `dist/` containing `index.html` and `assets/*.js`
+- [ ] `npm run preview` serves the built `dist/` without error
+- [ ] `npx tsc --noEmit` exits 0
+- [ ] `npx vitest run` still passes (no test regressions)
+
+---
+
+## Alternatives
+
+| Approach | Pros | Cons | Rejection Reason |
+|----------|------|------|------------------|
+| Use a bundler-rendered HTML template (e.g., vite-plugin-html) | More flexible; can inject env vars | Adds dependency; ph.1 deliverable is minimal | Research recommends plain static HTML |
+| Put Canvas DPR handling in `src/main.ts` now | Avoids revisiting in ph.6 | Out of scope; ph.1 doesn't draw real tiles | Belongs in ph.6 with resize listener |
+| Inline all styles in `src/main.ts` instead of `<style>` tag | Single source of truth for styling | Couples presentation with logic; later phases will need CSS for HUD/responsive layout anyway | Keep CSS in `index.html` for now; refactor to a `.css` file in ph.6 if needed |
+
+---
+
+## Risk Assessment
+
+| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |
+|------|------------|--------|------------|
+| Vite's default port 5173 is in use on dev machine | Low | Low | `vite --port` flag in npm script; not needed for c3 | 
+| `image-rendering: pixelated` doesn't work on Safari | Low | Low | Fallback to `crisp-edges` in ph.6 if needed; not blocking c3 |
+| `Intent` type in `src/types.ts` is incomplete (ph.2 may need more variants) | Medium | Low | Ph.2 will extend `Intent`; type union is additive — adding variants doesn't break callers |
