+# Proposal: entry-canvas
+
+> This document is a Change Proposal — align intent, scope, and approach before implementation.
+
+---
+
+## Intent
+
+Add the project entry point — `index.html`, `src/main.ts`, and `src/types.ts` — so `npm run dev` boots a browser showing a canvas and `npm run build` produces a deployable `dist/`. Without this, no game code can run.
+
+1. **What problem**: After c2, the project has config files but no entry point. `vite build` errors with `Cannot resolve entry module index.html`. `npm run dev` has nothing to serve.
+2. **Who is affected**: developers / CI. The build pipeline is non-functional.
+3. **If we don't make this change**: ph.2+ cannot begin; ph.1 deliverable (`npm run dev` boots browser canvas) fails.
+4. **Type**: prerequisite.
+5. **Linkage**: required by ph.1 deliverable; required by ph.2+ (core engine needs `src/types.ts` for shared types).
+
+---
+
+## Scope
+
+### In scope
+
+- Create `index.html` with `<canvas id="game">` + `<div id="hud">` placeholder + script tag for `src/main.ts`
+- Create `src/main.ts` that gets the canvas, sets its size, logs "Sokoban ready" to console, draws a placeholder rectangle on the canvas to confirm rendering works
+- Create `src/types.ts` with the `Direction` enum (used by later phases for move intents) and placeholder exports for `Coord`, `Tile` (kept as interfaces only — no runtime code needed yet)
+- Verify `npm run dev` boots a browser with the canvas visible
+- Verify `npm run build` produces `dist/` with `index.html` and JS bundle
+- Verify `npm run preview` serves the built `dist/`
+
+### Out of scope
+
+- Game logic (move, push, win, undo) — ph.2
+- Level data + loader — ph.3
+- Real renderer drawing tiles — ph.3
+- Keyboard input handling — ph.3
+- gameShell orchestrator — ph.3
+- HUD content (move count, level name) — ph.3+ (placeholder DOM only here)
+- Animations — ph.5
+- Touch / mobile — ph.6
+- localStorage persistence — ph.7
+
+---
+
+## Approach
+
+A minimal entry point that proves the build pipeline works end-to-end and gives later phases a place to plug into.
+
+**`index.html`**:
+- Single `<canvas id="game">` (per architecture research — Canvas for game world, DOM for HUD)
+- `<div id="hud">` placeholder (empty for now)
+- `<script type="module" src="/src/main.ts"></script>` — Vite handles the module resolution
+
+**`src/main.ts`**:
+- Import nothing (no game logic yet)
+- Get canvas via `document.getElementById('game')`
+- Set `canvas.width` and `canvas.height` to a default 480×480
+- Call `getContext('2d')`, fill with a solid color to confirm rendering works
+- Log "Sokoban ready" to console
+- No rAF loop, no state, no game logic — just prove the pipeline works
+
+**`src/types.ts`**:
+- `export type Direction = 'N' | 'S' | 'E' | 'W'` (used by all move logic in ph.2+)
+- `export interface Coord { x: number; y: number }` (used by reducer, renderer)
+- `export type Tile = 'floor' | 'wall' | 'target'` (used by level data)
+- No runtime code; pure types
+
+**No external libraries** — `src/main.ts` is plain DOM + Canvas 2D.
+
+---
+
+## Must-haves
+
+1. MUST contain `index.html` at repo root with `<canvas id="game">` and `<div id="hud">` elements, plus a module script tag for `/src/main.ts`.
+2. MUST contain `src/main.ts` that gets the canvas, sets its size, calls `getContext('2d')`, draws a visible rectangle, and logs "Sokoban ready" to console.
+3. MUST contain `src/types.ts` exporting `Direction`, `Coord`, and `Tile` types.
+4. MUST make `npm run build` exit 0 and produce a `dist/` directory containing `index.html` and a JS bundle.
+5. MUST make `npm run dev` boot a Vite dev server without error (full browser interaction not testable in this environment, but the dev server starting is verifiable).
+
+---
+
+## Non-goals
+
+- Not drawing any real game tiles (ph.3).
+- Not wiring keyboard input (ph.3).
+- Not implementing any game state or reducer (ph.2+).
+- Not implementing HUD content beyond a placeholder DOM container (ph.3+).
+- Not setting up the game loop or animator (ph.5).
+- Not touching touch input or mobile (ph.6).
