+# Design: toolchain-and-types
+
+> Technical design for the toolchain bootstrap change.
+
+---
+
+## Context & Goals
+
+This change is the prerequisite for every other change in the project — it produces the `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `.nvmrc`, and `.gitignore` that allow later changes to `npm install`, run TypeScript checks, and exclude build artifacts from version control. No source code is introduced; only build / tooling configuration.
+
+**Constraints** (from `bp/research/stack.md` and `ph.1-foundation/context.md`):
+- Exact pinned versions: Vite 8.1.2, TypeScript 5.6, Vitest 4.1.9, happy-dom 20.10.6, Node 20.19+
+- Strict TypeScript (`strict`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, `noImplicitOverride`) — applied from the start so every later file inherits the discipline
+- ESM (`"type": "module"`) to align with Vite 8 / Vitest 4 defaults
+- `private: true` to prevent accidental npm publish
+
+**Core goals** (3):
+1. `npm install` exits 0 and produces a committed `package-lock.json`
+2. `npx tsc --noEmit` runs cleanly against the empty `src/` and `tests/` skeleton (verified in c3 / c4)
+3. `.gitignore` excludes every build artifact path that any later phase produces
+
+---
+
+## Technical Approach
+
+This change produces **no source modules** — only configuration files. There is no architecture diagram or data flow to draw; the only artifacts are static files interpreted by npm, TypeScript, and git.
+
+### File Manifest
+
+| File Path | Description | Action |
+|-----------|-------------|--------|
+| `package.json` | npm manifest: `private`, `type: module`, `engines`, scripts, devDependencies | Create |
+| `tsconfig.json` | TypeScript project config: strict + bundler resolution + ES2022 + DOM lib + Vite client types | Create |
+| `tsconfig.node.json` | TS config for Vite/Vitest config files (Node + `@types/node`) | Create |
+| `.nvmrc` | Node version pin: `20.19.0` | Create |
+| `.gitignore` | Exclude build + test artifacts + env files + OS files | Create |
+| `package-lock.json` | Generated by `npm install`; committed for reproducibility | Create (via npm) |
+
+### Implementation Order
+
+1. Create `.gitignore` first (so subsequent file creations don't accidentally add artifacts).
+2. Create `.nvmrc` so future Node version checks are documented.
+3. Create `tsconfig.json` and `tsconfig.node.json` together (they reference each other).
+4. Create `package.json` last (so all referenced packages and scripts are correct).
+5. Run `npm install` to produce `package-lock.json`.
+6. Verify: `node --version` matches `.nvmrc`; `npx tsc --noEmit` runs without error against the (still empty) project; `cat package-lock.json | head` shows expected packages.
+
+### Key Configuration Decisions
+
+**`tsconfig.json`** (already locked by D3 in context.md):
+- `moduleResolution: 'bundler'` — required for `import.meta.glob` typing used by `level/loader.ts` in ph.3
+- `target: 'ES2022'` — modern enough for all browser targets; aligns with Vite 8 default
+- `strict: true` + `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true` — catches the most likely game-loop bug class (untyped grid coordinate access)
+- `verbatimModuleSyntax: true` — forces explicit `import type` for type-only imports; clean module boundary enforcement
+- `types: ['vite/client']` — provides `import.meta.env` and `import.meta.glob` typings
+- `include: ['src', 'tests']` — matches where later phases add code
+
+**`tsconfig.node.json`** (referenced by main tsconfig via `references`):
+- `composite: true` — required for project references
+- `module: 'ESNext'`, `moduleResolution: 'bundler'`
+- `types: ['node']` — for `process.env` access in `vite.config.ts`
+- `include: ['vite.config.ts', 'vitest.config.ts', '*.config.ts']` — covers all config files
+
+**`package.json` scripts**:
+- `dev`: `vite` — runs Vite dev server on default port 5173
+- `build`: `tsc -b && vite build` — type-check both projects, then bundle
+- `preview`: `vite preview` — serves `dist/` for E2E tests (used in ph.8)
+- `test`: `vitest` — interactive watch mode (default)
+- `test:run`: `vitest run` — CI-friendly single-run mode (exits non-zero on failure)
+
+**`.gitignore`** (standard Vite + Vitest + Playwright set):
+- `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `coverage/`, `playwright-report/`, `test-results/`
+- `.env*` with `!.env.example` exception
+- `.DS_Store`, `*.log`, `*.tsbuildinfo`
+
+---
+
+## Test Strategy
+
+No tests in this change. The smoke test that proves Vitest works is in c4. The type-check that proves `tsconfig.json` is sound is the `npx tsc --noEmit` verification step below.
+
+### Verification
+
+- [ ] `node --version` outputs `v20.19.x`
+- [ ] `npm install` exits 0
+- [ ] `npx tsc --noEmit` exits 0 (will only succeed once c3 adds `src/main.ts`; c1 verifies it does not error on empty config)
+- [ ] `cat .gitignore` lists all required patterns
+- [ ] `cat .nvmrc` is exactly `20.19.0`
+- [ ] `package-lock.json` exists and is committed
+
+---
+
+## Alternatives
+
+| Approach | Pros | Cons | Rejection Reason |
+|----------|------|------|------------------|
+| Use `pnpm` or `bun` instead of `npm` | Faster install; stricter lockfile | Requirement locked to `npm` (NFR) | Violates locked decision |
+| Use `tsconfig.json` with `noEmit: true` for src and a separate emit config | Simpler initially | Breaks `tsc -b && vite build` script flow | Vite docs recommend project references for config files; cleaner |
+| Pin Vite to `^7` for broader Node compat | Avoids Node 20.19 requirement | Vite 7 is current-LTS-1; Vite 8 is current; no compatibility reason | Research.md recommends ^8.1.2; using it from the start avoids a forced upgrade later |
+| Add `@commitlint/cli`, `@commitlint/config-conventional`, `husky` in ph.1 | Catches bad commits early | Out of scope for ph.1 per D8 in context.md | Belongs in ph.9 |
+
+---
+
+## Risk Assessment
+
+| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |
+|------|------------|--------|------------|
+| `npm install` fails due to peer-dep conflict between Vite 8 / Vitest 4 / happy-dom | Low | High | Verified peer ranges in research.md; if conflict, fallback to Vite 7 + Vitest 4 is documented |
+| `.nvmrc` mismatch on developer machines (older Node) | Medium | Low | `.nvmrc` documents `20.19.0`; engines field rejects install on older Node |
+| `tsconfig.node.json` circular reference with main tsconfig | Low | Medium | Use `references` array (TS project references) instead of `extends`; well-documented pattern |
+| `package-lock.json` drift on subsequent installs | Low | Low | Commit lockfile; CI runs `npm ci` (not `npm install`) for reproducibility |
