+# Proposal: toolchain-and-types
+
+> This document is a Change Proposal — align intent, scope, and approach before implementation. Complete each section; reviewers will evaluate this proposal before the design phase.
+
+---
+
+## Intent
+
+Bootstrap the npm + TypeScript toolchain for the sokoban project so all later changes (c2: build/test configs, c3: canvas entry, c4: smoke test, plus all M1-M3 phases) can build, lint, and run on a known foundation.
+
+1. **What problem**: Project currently has only `bp/` (planning artifacts), `.git/`, `.omp/`, `.serena/`. No `package.json`, no `tsconfig.json`, no source code. Cannot `npm run dev`, `npm test`, or `npm run build`.
+2. **Who is affected**: developers / CI (which doesn't exist yet). The user cannot run the game until a toolchain exists.
+3. **If we don't make this change**: Every subsequent phase (c2, c3, c4, ph.2-ph.10) is blocked at its first step.
+4. **Type**: foundation / tech debt elimination / prerequisite for the entire project.
+5. **Linkage**: required by `bp/roadmap.md` ph.1-foundation deliverable; required by every change in ph.1-foundation plus all 9 later phases.
+
+---
+
+## Scope
+
+### In scope
+
+- Create `package.json` declaring `"private": true`, `"type": "module"`, and `"engines.node": ">=20.19.0"` with scripts and devDependencies
+- Create `tsconfig.json` with strict TypeScript settings (`strict`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, `noImplicitOverride`, `moduleResolution: 'bundler'`, `target: 'ES2022'`, `lib: ['ES2022', 'DOM']`)
+- Create `tsconfig.node.json` for compiling Vite/Vitest config files (per Vite 8 recommendation)
+- Create `.nvmrc` pinning Node to `20.19.0`
+- Create `.gitignore` excluding `node_modules`, `dist`, `coverage`, `playwright-report`, `test-results`, `.env*`, `.DS_Store`
+- Add all locked devDependencies per `bp/research/stack.md`: `vite ^8.1.2`, `typescript ^5.6`, `vitest ^4.1.9`, `happy-dom ^20.10.6`, `@types/node ^20`
+- Run `npm install` to produce `package-lock.json`
+- Add `"prepare"` script deferred (no husky yet — added in ph.9)
+
+### Out of scope
+
+- `vite.config.ts` and `vitest.config.ts` content (change c2)
+- `index.html`, `src/main.ts`, `src/types.ts` (change c3)
+- `tests/unit/smoke.test.ts` (change c4)
+- ESLint / Prettier config (ph.9)
+- Husky / commitlint hooks (ph.9)
+- Conventional Commits enforcement (ph.9)
+- Lockfile for browserslist / can-i-use (ph.9 if needed)
+
+---
+
+## Approach
+
+Standard Vite + TypeScript ESM project layout. The toolchain is the foundation that all later changes build on; it must be minimal but complete enough that c2-c4 can each add their pieces without re-touching `package.json`.
+
+**Architecture layer**: build / tooling layer only. No source modules yet.
+
+**Library choices** (all locked by `bp/research/stack.md`):
+- `vite ^8.1.2` (build + dev server; current as of 2026-07-01 per verified npm registry)
+- `typescript ^5.6` (latest stable; supports `verbatimModuleSyntax` + `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`)
+- `vitest ^4.1.9` (peer-compatible with Vite 6/7/8 per its declared peer range; matches Vite 8)
+- `happy-dom ^20.10.6` (Vitest-recommended default; fast)
+- `@types/node ^20` (required for Vite config files in TS)
+
+**Data flow**: none yet — no source code.
+
+**Compatibility**: fresh project, no migration concerns. Setting `"engines.node": ">=20.19.0"` documents the Vite 8 minimum.
+
+**Testability**: smoke test wired in c4 will exercise Vitest; no test seams needed in this change.
+
+---
+
+## Must-haves
+
+1. MUST contain a `package.json` at repo root with `"private": true`, `"type": "module"`, and `"engines": { "node": ">=20.19.0" }`.
+2. MUST declare all locked devDependencies (`vite ^8.1.2`, `typescript ^5.6`, `vitest ^4.1.9`, `happy-dom ^20.10.6`, `@types/node ^20`) and no others.
+3. MUST define scripts: `dev` (vite), `build` (tsc -b && vite build), `preview` (vite preview), `test` (vitest), `test:run` (vitest run).
+4. MUST contain a `tsconfig.json` enabling `strict: true`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`, `noImplicitOverride: true`, `target: "ES2022"`, `moduleResolution: "bundler"`, `module: "ESNext"`, `lib: ["ES2022", "DOM"]`, `types: ["vite/client"]`, with `include: ["src", "tests"]`.
+5. MUST contain a `tsconfig.node.json` referencing the main tsconfig and including `vite.config.ts`, `vitest.config.ts`, and `*.config.ts` files, with `@types/node` types.
+6. MUST contain `.nvmrc` with the single line `20.19.0`.
+7. MUST contain `.gitignore` excluding at minimum: `node_modules`, `dist`, `coverage`, `playwright-report`, `test-results`, `.env*`, `.DS_Store`.
+8. MUST result in `npm install` exiting with code 0 and producing `package-lock.json`.
+
+---
+
+## Non-goals
+
+- Not introducing ESLint, Prettier, or any linting tool in this change (ph.9).
+- Not introducing husky, commitlint, or any commit hooks in this change (ph.9).
+- Not setting up CI workflows (ph.9).
+- Not creating the Vite or Vitest config files (c2).
+- Not creating the HTML entry point or any TypeScript source (c3).
+- Not creating any tests (c4).
+- Not initializing any level data or game logic (later phases).
