+# Design: vite-vitest-configs
+
+> Technical design for adding Vite and Vitest config files.
+
+---
+
+## Context & Goals
+
+This change completes the toolchain by adding the two config files that `tsconfig.node.json` already references. Without them, `tsc -b` errors and `npm run build` cannot run.
+
+**Constraints** (from `bp/research/stack.md` and `ph.1-foundation/context.md`):
+- Vite 8.1.2, Vitest 4.1.9 — current as of 2026-07-01
+- Env-driven `base` for Vite (per context.md D4, future-flipped to `/sokoban/` in ph.9)
+- Scoped happy-dom for Vitest tests matching `*-dom.test.ts` pattern (per context.md D5)
+
+**Core goals** (3):
+1. `npx tsc -b` exits 0 (c1's TS18003 error resolved)
+2. `npm run build` produces a deployable `dist/`
+3. Existing smoke test still passes under `npx vitest run`
+
+---
+
+## Technical Approach
+
+Two config files using TypeScript:
+
+### `vite.config.ts`
+
+```ts
+import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
+
+export default defineConfig({
+  base: process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE ?? '/',
+});
+```
+
+- `defineConfig` from `vite` provides type-safety
+- `process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE ?? '/'` — env-driven per context.md D4; defaults to `/` for dev/local, ph.9 sets the production default
+- No plugins needed — Vite 8 handles TS, JSON, and CSS out of the box; `import.meta.glob` (used in ph.3) is built-in
+- No `build` config — defaults are fine for a single-page Canvas game
+
+### `vitest.config.ts`
+
+```ts
+import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';
+
+export default defineConfig({
+  test: {
+    projects: [
+      {
+        test: {
+          name: 'unit',
+          include: ['tests/unit/**/*.test.ts'],
+          exclude: ['tests/unit/**/*-dom.test.ts'],
+        },
+      },
+      {
+        test: {
+          name: 'unit-dom',
+          environment: 'happy-dom',
+          include: ['tests/unit/**/*-dom.test.ts'],
+        },
+      },
+    ],
+  },
+});
+```
+
+- `defineConfig` from `vitest/config` (not `vite`) — gives typed access to the `test` field
+- Vitest 4 **removed** `environmentMatchGlobs` (was a Vitest 2/3 feature). Replacement: the `projects` API, where each project specifies its own `environment` and `include` glob.
+- Two projects: `unit` (default `node` env, all tests except `*-dom.test.ts`) and `unit-dom` (`happy-dom`, only `*-dom.test.ts`).
+- Pure logic tests stay fast in `node`; DOM-touching tests get the `happy-dom` env when added.
+- The smoke test (`tests/unit/smoke.test.ts`) matches `unit` project and runs in node env.
+
+### Implementation Order
+
+1. Create `vite.config.ts` first (needed for `tsc -b` to pass)
+2. Create `vitest.config.ts` second (also needed for `tsc -b`)
+3. Run `npx tsc -b` to verify the composite build passes
+4. Run `npm run build` to verify `dist/` is produced
+5. Run `npx vitest run` to verify smoke test still passes
+
+---
+
+## File Manifest
+
+| File Path | Description | Action |
+|-----------|-------------|--------|
+| `vite.config.ts` | Vite build config; env-driven base | Create |
+| `vitest.config.ts` | Vitest config; happy-dom scoped to `-dom.test.ts` | Create |
+
+---
+
+## Test Strategy
+
+No tests in this change. The existing smoke test (`tests/unit/smoke.test.ts` from c1) verifies Vitest still works. `npx tsc -b` verifies the TypeScript composite build works.
+
+### Verification
+
+- [ ] `npx tsc -b` exits 0
+- [ ] `npm run build` exits 0; `dist/` directory created
+- [ ] `npx vitest run` exits 0; smoke test still passes
+- [ ] Both config files export `defineConfig(...)` results
+
+---
+
+## Alternatives
+
+| Approach | Pros | Cons | Rejection Reason |
+|----------|------|------|------------------|
+| Inline Vitest config in `vite.config.ts` via `test` block | One fewer file; Vitest 4 supports this | Mixes build config with test config; harder to test in isolation; conflicts with research recommendation of separate files | Explicit separate file is cleaner |
+| Use `.js` config files instead of `.ts` | Simpler TS setup; no composite project needed | Loses type-safety on `defineConfig`; research recommends TS configs to align with project source language | TS configs match project language |
+| Set `base: '/'` hardcoded | Simpler | Violates context.md D4 (env-driven shape established for ph.9 to flip) | Defers a needed refactor to ph.9 |
+
+---
+
+## Risk Assessment
+
+| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |
+|------|------------|--------|------------|
+| `process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE` typing breaks strict TS | Low | Low | `@types/node` already provides `process.env` typing; `?? '/'` provides fallback |
+| `tsc -b` still fails for unrelated reasons | Low | Medium | If `outDir` in `tsconfig.node.json` from c1 needs adjusting, fix and re-verify |
+| `dist/` is committed accidentally | Low | Low | `.gitignore` already excludes `dist/` (from c1) |
