+# Proposal: vite-vitest-configs
+
+> This document is a Change Proposal — align intent, scope, and approach before implementation.
+
+---
+
+## Intent
+
+Add the Vite and Vitest config files so the project's build (`npm run build`) and test (`npm test`) scripts can resolve their configuration. Without these files, `tsc -b` errors with TS18003 (no inputs in `tsconfig.node.json`), `npm run build` fails, and `vitest` runs without scoped DOM environment.
+
+1. **What problem**: c1 created `tsconfig.node.json` (composite project referencing Vite/Vitest config files) but the actual config files don't exist. `tsc -b` fails; `npm run build` won't run; `vitest` lacks the documented environment scoping.
+2. **Who is affected**: developers / CI. The `build` and `test` scripts in `package.json` are unusable without these configs.
+3. **If we don't make this change**: c3 cannot be verified end-to-end (`tsc -b` would fail); ph.2 (core engine) cannot ship; ph.8 E2E cannot run.
+4. **Type**: prerequisite / tech debt elimination.
+5. **Linkage**: required by every subsequent change in ph.1-foundation (c3) and all later phases.
+
+---
+
+## Scope
+
+### In scope
+
+- Create `vite.config.ts` with env-driven `base` per `ph.1-foundation/context.md` D4
+- Create `vitest.config.ts` with `environmentMatchGlobs` to scope happy-dom per `ph.1-foundation/context.md` D5
+- Verify `tsc -b` exits 0 (was failing with TS18003 in c1)
+- Verify `npm run build` produces `dist/`
+
+### Out of scope
+
+- `index.html`, `src/main.ts`, `src/types.ts` (c3)
+- Source-level game code (later phases)
+- Level data (ph.3+)
+- Renderer / input / animation modules (later phases)
+
+---
+
+## Approach
+
+Two config files using TypeScript and Vite 8 / Vitest 4 idioms. Both reference `@types/node` and use `process.env`.
+
+**`vite.config.ts`**: minimal config; defines `base` from `process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE` (defaults to `'/'` in ph.1; flipped to `'/sokoban/'` in ph.9). No plugins yet — ph.3 will add level-related assets via `import.meta.glob` (no plugin needed).
+
+**`vitest.config.ts`**: extends Vitest 4 config with `environmentMatchGlobs` to scope happy-dom to `**/*-dom.test.ts` files. Pure logic tests stay in `node` env (faster).
+
+**Compatibility**: both configs are TS files; `tsconfig.node.json` already includes them via glob `*.config.ts`. No additional type setup needed.
+
+**Testability**: vitest config itself is verified by running `npx vitest run` (already passes from c1's smoke test); the change shouldn't break it.
+
+---
+
+## Must-haves
+
+1. MUST contain a `vite.config.ts` at repo root that exports a `defineConfig({...})` result with `base: process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE ?? '/'`.
+2. MUST contain a `vitest.config.ts` at repo root that uses Vitest 4's `projects` API to scope happy-dom to `tests/unit/**/*-dom.test.ts` files, with a default `unit` project for pure logic tests.
+3. MUST make `npx tsc -b` exit 0 (the c1 TS18003 error must be resolved by the existence of these config files).
+4. MUST NOT break the existing smoke test (`npx vitest run` still exits 0 with 1/1 passing).
+5. (Deferred to c3) `npm run build` exit 0 and `dist/` produced — requires `index.html` which is c3's deliverable.
+
+---
+
+## Non-goals
+
+- Not configuring any Vite plugins yet (ph.3 will use `import.meta.glob` natively).
+- Not configuring test coverage (ph.8 may add).
+- Not configuring path aliases (not needed — Vite defaults suffice).
+- Not adding the GitHub Pages base default value `/sokoban/` (ph.9).
+- Not setting up ESLint or other tooling (ph.9).
